						<summary>

						<p>Pillar of the <hi rend="italic">mukha-maṇḍapa</hi> in the Viṭṭhaēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>1144 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1066, Māgha ba. 14, Tuesday. The cyclic year being the Raktāshi and the details of the date correspond to 1144 A.D., January 23.</p>						

						<p>Incomplete. Records the gift of the perpetual lamp to the temple of Viṭṭīśvaradēva of Bhaṭṭiprōlu by Gaḍivana Gōkana for the merit of his parents. The lamps were entrusted to <hi rend="italic">aṁgarika</hi> Tumuka and <hi rend="italic">naṁgarika</hi> Aṁgarikarole with the stipulation to supply one <hi rend="italic">māna</hi> of ghee everyday.</p>						

						</summary>
